{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d9ba164d-09ee-45ad-ac11-020aad80fafd","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options:**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single org\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Minimal API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# No auth (add JWT Bearer manually later)\ndotnet new webapi\n```\n\nFor JWT Bearer auth without Azure AD, create with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` via NuGet manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"baae61a9-c501-4709-a9ab-55eab2b10fb1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/web development question. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge without needing to search the filesystem, since the working directory appears to be empty and this is a general knowledge question.","outputTokens":334,"requestId":"D00A:1E4C:63C787:7432A4:69F93E7A"},"id":"85f35ee4-0206-472a-ba26-d7fda0228cac","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:06.874Z","parentId":"aaf79fb5-4bc3-4d24-82cf-609ab6a94d43"}
